'\"macro stdmacro
.TH TMPFILE 3S 
.SH NAME
tmpfile \- create a temporary file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <stdio.h>
.PP
.B
.SM FILE
.B "\(**tmpfile (\|)"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Tmpfile\^
creates a temporary file and returns a
corresponding
.SM FILE
pointer.
The file will
automatically be deleted when the process using
it terminates.
The file is opened for update.
.SH SEE ALSO
creat(2), unlink(2), fopen(3S), mktemp(3C), tmpnam(3S).
